task.summary: woohoo Dungeon is being generated properly and it can be navigated

Dungeon builder now works and properly generates a full dungeon of rooms from the details of the map in the dungeon class. I had to expose the map to access it's details. Updated the config files to include the missing input maps. Built a resource dictionary from strings of room details to RoomTypeCollection.Types(These are different than the ones in the model, confusing I know) that can be passed into another dictionary for scenes of rooms.
deleted the assemblyinfo.cs in the tests project to get rid of compiler error related to duplicate assembly references
hopefully got rid of the duplicate assembly attributes error
Dungeon builder has the items and inventory fully functional. You can see the effect of vision potion when clicking on it. Health potion also works.
You can now attack and kill enemies. It's not fun, but it works.
Traps work and generate in the dungeon at the correct position.
Pushing all files to see if it will break anything
